      "text": "**Farmers Grievances** "
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "6d6f1ee3be7e8a36",
      "text": "**i)**\tMoving cattle into farms and destroying crops etc. This is the usual accusation against Bororo Fulanis. Although they often deny it, is an accusation which proves to be true most of the time;"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "909534dfaa1f5c52",
      "text": "**ii)**\tUprooting cassava and yam tubers for feeding of cattle. When pressed for fodder for their herds, Bororos go into the farms and uproot available crops to feed their animals. They even break down bans and feed their cattle with the stored products.  Also, the ponds and any other sources of water are polluted; "
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2604d8ac93a955ef",
      "text": "**iii)**\tAssault with dangerous weapons on owners of such farms who dared to challenge them. Such assault have resulted in maiming, rape and even death. At Amoko village, a girl of about 13years old was allegedly raped by a group of Bororo herdsmen. Also at Ajelanwa and Yemiri villages, Bororo herdsmen intentionally and maliciously grazed their cattle in farms and devoured crops. Other settlements affected include, Ataye, Aba Omopupa, Irawo, Baasi, Oje-Owode, Ofiki, Corner- Owo, Tede. Even the Local Government cashew farm at Orogun near Saki was invaded and destroyed."
