      "id": "c356b8351780441f",
      "text": "**i)** There was a case of a foreign Bororo Fulani cattle rearer who grazed on a farm along Ekokan and disappeared unhurt. There was reprisal attack two weeks later during which an apparently innocent Bororo fulani found grazing in the periphery of a previously invaded farm was beaten up while his luggage and other belongings were seized and his herds of cattle scattered."
    },
